Name: Maginot Cannon
Phrase: Ma, Magi...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: It was gone after the last hit...

Name: Queensway
Phrase: You mean that giant weapon was an illusion too?

Name: Amiens
Phrase: But the magic in the ruins that was there disappeared. The Mist Monsters and minecarts that were rampaging above may also have disappeared.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: So that enemy called the Maginot Cannon, was the source of the Phantom Mist then?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Vivienne, did you miss not having Yoshino around?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Oui, I did miss you.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: I really missed you, I missed you so much, that I was almost losing my mind!

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: OOOOOH!? Vivienne, that place you're touching is not the tail, that's the butt. Not for mofumofu!

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: But the ducts in the ceiling were like a maze. If you weren't for you blowing your whistle, I'm sure I would still be tailing Yoshino's ass all day.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: I'm really glad you two are safe. But how did you know there was a way out?

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Considering the timing of our rendezvous, Miss Yakutsk and Miss Yoshino must have escaped from the terminal soon afterwards, right? Is it that easy to find an escape route?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: That's the thing, it's what those two boys I've met in the forest told me.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: You mean Mr. Karl and Mr. Emil?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yes, Karl told us to look for the iron floorboards if we got trapped in the Minecart Graveyard.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: After we got everyone down there, we found the iron floorboards right away. There was a hidden passage under the terminal. We went into the ducts that were in that passageway and went to the lower level.

Name: Amiens
Phrase: A hidden passage! That sounds very archaeological! What kind of mechanisms were there in that hidden passageway!?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Well, there were no traps of any kind. Instead, there were a lot of weapons and ordnance lying around. I think it was an emergency storeroom.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: So that's where Miss Yakutsk picked up the gun that you fired with.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: It says 'Étienne MAS-36' on it!

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: WHA, what's that all of a sudden!?

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Étienne MAS-36? I've never heard of it.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: I mean, does it really say that?

Name: Paddington
Phrase: What? It's written on it, see? Look, right over here...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Everybody, let's talk after leaving the ruins. We have to get out to the surface somehow!

Name: Putra
Phrase: Yes, let's get Yoshino to take a look at that minecart we saw earlier! There's some kind of mechanism that we don't understand, and if we can move it, we can use it to escape, can't we?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Oooooh-, can take care of that sort of thing.

Name: Rouen
Phrase: That talking self-propelled artillery just now dropped something.

Name: Amiens
Phrase: A self-propelled artillery can hold items now...?

Name: Rouen
Phrase: This is a map. I wonder if it represents the whole site.

Name: Amiens
Phrase: And this one is...

Name: Amiens
Phrase: This is a device powered by mist stones! Conductor, look at this! There's a mist stone here!
Amiens found a mysterious mechanical device that was processed from mist stones. It appears to be a power-generating device combining iron parts and a mist stone.
However, a mist stone of this size cannot even move a single cart. It would be impossible to consider it as a power source for the entire ruins.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Hmm hmm... This is a very interesting device.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Like this, and like this? Connect the wires, and twist the knob...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Lever, On!

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Wha!? What happened!?

Name: Rouen
Phrase: I can feel the electric power of the God of Thunder...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Mufufu, looks like Yoshino has done it. Used the sacred something power!

Name: Amiens
Phrase: The cart has been activated! There's energy supplied to it!

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: This is the location that controls power. It's generating very strong energy without using mist stones.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: How in the world did they do it without using mist stones, fire or water...?

Name: Paddington
Phrase: That would be lightning!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Lightning?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Speaking of, the cipher Rouen and Amiens initially solved did say to look for 'Éclair'.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Yes, the map of the ruins dropped by Maginot Cannon had many of the words from that cipher on it.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Technically, that word is not 'Éclair' but 'Électricité'. I think it is better interpreted as 'electricity generated by lightning'!

Name: Paddington
Phrase: The language used at this site is close to ancient Verforench, but it's slightly different. This is a cipher text combining the local language developed in the east and a fictional language used within the biography of the elven tribes.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: This is the language that Rouen called fake. The three missing words were 'Chariot', 'Chambre' and 'Contrôle'. If we combine this with the deciphered cipher and add the missing letters to make it work, we get the following sentence:
'The guardian of Ouvrage Schoenenbourg is isolated. Find the room that controls electricity and move the cart.'

Name: Paddington
Phrase: This is the Divine Child of St. Iris's Sacred Holy Power!

Name: Putra
Phrase: No way, you're way too awesome...

Name: Amiens
Phrase: Mademoiselle Paddington, how do you know so much about ancient languages? You've just said that the fictional language in the biography of the elven tribes is a made-up language, right?

Name: Paddington
Phrase: I've read about it in books!

Name: Rouen
Phrase: Read it in books... Do you even realize how many thousands of books there are on elvish biography alone!?

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Things that I've seen just once will never be forgotten ever again!

Name: Amiens
Phrase: Wow, is that what's called rote memory ability...

Name: Rouen
Phrase: I concede defeat. The Divine Child of St. Iris is way too amazing...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: A-Anyway! The cart works, so let's get the Hell out of here!

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Yoshino, just to confirm, we can all go together this time, right?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: No problem, because this minecart has a control panel.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Good...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Come, get on, everybody! Let's quickly leave this rust-stenched iron-fortress ruins!
On Vivienne's signal, the entire Special Steel Squad gets on the minecart. Unlike the lift we saw earlier, all nine of us are on board.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Well then, shuupatsu shinko~!

Name: Putra
Phrase: OOOOH-!

Name: Putra
Phrase: Ummm... why is this so freaking slow?

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Even I can limp faster than this with my injured leg...

Name: Rouen
Phrase: Hey Conductor, why don't you try using the mist stone from earlier? There's a blueprint of this minecart here. Says that it can go faster if you put a booster on the power unit.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Perhaps it might go even faster if Sir Conductor injects magic power into it.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: The iron minecart, injected with iron~♪
I see. So it's a similar principle to the Mist Train. Very well, let me try this booster thing.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: T-that's strong power-!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Uh, I think I have a bad feeling about this...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Hold tight, everybody! We're blasting all the way out of the ruins!

Name: Paddington
Phrase: The Mist Minecart is departing towards the surface!
The minecart escaped from the mysterious ruins of Ouvrage Schoenenbourg all the way to the surface, where the beautiful forest landscape of Verforet unfolds.

Once on the ground, the Train Knights squinted at the dazzling light spilling through the trees. They saw that the forest looked completely different from the view they had seen from the tochka, and knew that the source of the Phantom Mist that had covered the area had been extinguished.
The grey tochkas that ruined the landscape and the muddy trenches were nowhere to be seen. Even the minecart we had just ridden on had vanished without a trace when we looked back.
--The ruins of the Ouvrage Schoenenbourg itself were a mirage, from Phantom Mist.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Amiens, Rouen, come here for a moment.

Name: Amiens
Phrase: W-What is it, Mademoiselle Vivienne?

Name: Rouen
Phrase: We did well this time, didn't we? I don't think we did anything that would make you angry...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: What are you scared of? Did you think I was going to lecture you two?

Name: Amiens
Phrase: Because Vivienne is a veteran of the gendarmerie.

Name: Rouen
Phrase: Not just a senior too. You're the top ranger and a great mage that everyone admires.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Hmhmhm, I didn't know you two thought of me that way.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: It's true however you need a scolding to about that joke of a report. I'll report that to the gendarmerie higher-ups, and I'm sure they'll be very angry with you.

Name: Rouen
Phrase: Ugh, I went too far. I thought it was important to grab attention, so I went to...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: However, the two of you helped us a lot with this site investigation. Without you two, this forest could not have been saved.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: This is between you two and me only. I also wanted to show everyone in the SSS that I'm good when it comes to missions inside Verforet.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: But when it came to investigating the ruins, I was completely clueless. I felt inexperienced.

Name: Amiens
Phrase: But that's not true! You, Vivienne was leading the team!

Name: Rouen
Phrase: Yeah! Without Conductor and Vivienne, we wouldn't have made it this far.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Hmhmm, thank you. I love you both!

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: If we ever need help again in the future, please continue to lend a hand. As fellow members of the SSS. And as Verforench elves who love this forest.

Name: Amiens
Phrase: Of course!

Name: Rouen
Phrase: If we find interesting ruins, we can go exploring together.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Hey, Paddington, do you remember the map of the ruins that Rouen was holding earlier?

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Of course I do. I remember every detail perfectly.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Did you see the word 'Ouvrage Fermont' anywhere on that map? I recalled Karl and Emil mentioning it...

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Yes. There certainly was. There were three fortress names on that map: 'Ouvrage Schoenenbourg', 'Ouvrage Fermont' and then 'Ouvrage Thionville'.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: However, as the ruins have disappeared, there's no way to find out though...

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Yes, I know...

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Thanks Paddington.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: You're welcome! Please let me know if there's anything else you'd like to know.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: I wonder if Ouvrage Fermont and Thionville would have appeared had the ruins continued to expand...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yakutsk, it's about time to head back to the gendarmerie station, okay?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Yes, I'm on my way.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: ...Hey, Yoshino, Karl and Emil are still missing after all, right?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Un. Not even the Verforet Gendarmerie who were at the station have seen Karl and Emil.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: I wonder if those children lived in the same period as the ruins of Ouvrage Schoenenbourg...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Not sure about that.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: But they didn't look so bad to Yoshino.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: It's not so easy to decide if they're good or bad...

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Well, whatever. The ruins and the Phantom Mist are gone, so there's no point in thinking about it any more.
Did Karl and Emil, who Yakutsk and his friends say they saw, make it safely to the west of the forest...?
